You are the orchestrator. Spawn 4 sub-agents in parallel. Do not write code yourself until all sub-agents complete, then do the integration steps.

Context
Building a generic agentic platform on Google ADK (adk web). Day 1 domain: GitLab. Two agents: coordinator_agent routes to gitlab_workflow, which runs gitlab_agent. Tools are independent and self-registering — agents declare tool names in YAML, resolver looks them up from a global registry.
Shared contracts (all sub-agents must honor exactly)

ToolResult:       success:bool, data:Any, error:str|None, metadata:dict
CallbackSig:      (callback_context) -> LlmResponse | None
tool name format: {domain}_{operation}  e.g. gitlab_list_commits
session key fmt:  "{scope}:{key}"       e.g. "app:gitlab_default_project"


SUB-AGENT 1 — tool-and-registry
Build the tool foundation.
tools/base_tool.py
	∙	ToolResult dataclass: success, data, error, metadata
	∙	BaseTool ABC: name:str, description:str, requires_approval:bool=False, abstract execute(**kwargs)->ToolResult, concrete to_adk_function()->callable that wraps execute() as a plain Python function ADK can register as a tool
tools/registry.py
	∙	Module-level _registry: dict[str, BaseTool] = {}
	∙	register(tool: BaseTool) — raises ValueError if name already registered
	∙	get(name: str) -> BaseTool — raises KeyError with message "Tool '{name}' not found. Available: {list_all()}"
	∙	list_all() -> list[str]
	∙	get_many(names: list[str]) -> list[BaseTool]
tools/gitlab/gitlab_local.py
One class per operation extending BaseTool. Uses python-gitlab SDK. Reads GITLAB_URL, GITLAB_TOKEN, GITLAB_DEFAULT_PROJECT from env. Returns ToolResult always — never raises. Converts raw SDK responses via domains/gitlab/transformers.py.



