SUB-AGENT 3 — framework-callbacks-and-session
Build session manager, all 4 callbacks, and composer. Depends on ToolResult shape from Sub-Agent 1 — import only from tools.base_tool, nothing else from Sub-Agent 1.
framework/session_manager.py
Module-level singleton. Three scopes backed by plain dicts for Day 1.
	∙	session: — per-run, cleared after each run
	∙	user: — keyed by user_id, lives for process lifetime
	∙	app: — populated once at startup from env

class SessionManager:
    def get(self, scope_key: str, default=None)   # "app:gitlab_default_project"
    def set(self, scope_key: str, value)
    def clear_session_scope(self)
    def init_app_scope(self)   # reads env vars into app: keys

session_mgr = SessionManager()   # singleton


init_app_scope() populates:
	∙	app:tool_mode from TOOL_MODE env (default local)
	∙	app:gitlab_default_project from GITLAB_DEFAULT_PROJECT env
	∙	app:allowed_agents from ALLOWED_AGENTS env (default *)
framework/callbacks/before_agent_cb.py
Controller — returns LlmResponse to block or None to proceed.
	1.	Permission check: read app:allowed_agents from session_mgr. If not * and callback_context.agent.name not in list → return LlmResponse(content=[Part(text="Agent not permitted.")]).
	2.	Session injection: if agent is gitlab_agent, write callback_context.state['gitlab_default_project'] = session_mgr.get('app:gitlab_default_project').
framework/callbacks/after_agent_cb.py
Controller — returns None.
	1.	Write agent output to session: callback_context.state[f"{callback_context.agent.name}_output"] = callback_context.state.get('_output').
	2.	Set checkpoint: callback_context.state[f"checkpoint_{callback_context.agent.name}"] = True.
	3.	If agent is gitlab_agent and output has success=False, write callback_context.state['gitlab_last_error'] = output.error.
framework/callbacks/before_model_cb.py
Observer — returns None. Appends narration style to system instruction:
	∙	gitlab_agent → append "Think step by step. State which tool you will call and why."
	∙	all others → nothing
framework/callbacks/after_tool_cb.py
Observer — returns None. Appends one JSON line to reports/traces/tool_calls.jsonl:

{"agent": "...", "tool": "...", "success": true, "timestamp": "..."}


Creates file and parent dirs if they don’t exist.
framework/composer.py

CALLBACK_REGISTRY = {
    "before_agent_cb":  before_agent_cb,
    "after_agent_cb":   after_agent_cb,
    "before_model_cb":  before_model_cb,
    "after_tool_cb":    after_tool_cb,
}

def compose(names: list[str]) -> callable | None:
    # empty list → return None
    # one name → return function directly
    # multiple → return wrapper that calls each in order,
    #            returns first non-None (controller pattern)


