🧠 HOW THIS TREE WORKS (SIMPLE FLOW)

Normal planner request

API → orchestrator → runner
     → agents-config loads planner
     → tools loader builds tools (local + MCP + agents)
     → prompt_service runs reasoning
     → result validated by schemas
     → session saved


⸻

MCP tool call

planner → tools wrapper
       → mcp.execution_client.execute()
       → MCP server


⸻

Human-in-loop

planner returns status=needs_input
→ runner marks session paused
→ orchestrator.resume_session() later
→ runner runs same agent with updated history


⸻

Custom workflow

runner detects agent.type=workflow
→ loads class from custom_workflows/
→ workflow.run() executes


⸻

🟢 DESIGN PRINCIPLES THIS TREE FOLLOWS
	•	Runner = execution brain
	•	Orchestrator = lifecycle manager
	•	Tools = unified capability layer
	•	MCP = network client only
	•	Prompt service = only LLM access point
	•	Sessions = state + HITL memory
	•	Schemas = contracts enforced by runner

This keeps everything:
	•	modular
	•	testable
	•	scalable
	•	enterprise-safe

